WARRANTY DEED Vol. 130

LAWSON MAY
ALICE MAY
Husband and Wife TO
P. L. GUERS

Know All Men by these Presents: That we, Lawson May and Alice May, Husband and Wife, the Grantor_s, who claims title by or through instruments, recorded in volume 121 page 230

County Recorder's office, for the consideration of One Dollar and other valuable consideration Dollars ($1.00) received to our full satisfaction of P. L. Guers and Florence Guers, Husband and Wife the Grantee_s, whose tax mailing address will be Route #1, Bowerston, Ohio

Give, Grant, Bargain, Sell and Convey unto the said Grantee_s, their heirs and assigns, the following described premises, situated in the Township of Monroe County of Carroll and State of Ohio:

All the known as being a part of the Southwest Quarter of Section Twenty-five (25), Township thirteen (13), Range seven (7); beginning for boundary at a point in the middle of the graded road I.C.H. #76, which point is three hundred and two and eight tenths (302.8) feet south, thirty-seven (37) degrees West along the center line of said road, which is about twenty-three (23) chains westward from the quarter line running along the road; thence South 37 degrees West along the road 100 feet to the place of beginning; for the road boundary; thence continuing South 37 degrees West along the center of the road 83.5 feet; thence South 53 degrees West 101.5 feet to a post; thence North 37 degrees West 83.5 feet; thence North 53 degrees West 101.5 feet to the place of beginning, containing .237 of an acre, more or less.

[Additional standard deed language follows regarding holding, transferring, and warranty of the property]

Signed and acknowledged in Presence of:
Glenn L. Fortune
Glenn L. Fortune
Betty Guers

STATE OF OHIO
Carroll County, ss.

Signed: Lawson May
Alice May

Before me, a Notary Public in and for said County and State, personally appeared the above named Lawson May and Alice May who acknowledged that they did sign the foregoing instrument and that the same is their free act and deed.

In Testimony Whereof, I have hereunto set my hand and official seal at Carroll Co., Ohio, this 7th day of September A.D. 1954

Seal: Glenn L. Fortune, Notary Public
Glenn L. Fortune, Notary Public, State of Ohio
My Commission Expires December 21, 1956

Transferred: January 25, 1956
Received for Record: January 25, 1956 at 11:10 o'clock A.M.
Recorded: January 25, 1956

Fee $ 1.75

R. A. MacDonald, Recorder
